This paper discusses energy efficiency in cognitive radio networks, which involves topics related to network infrastructure, information theory, and system design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between energy consumption and throughput, which is a topic related to information theory and communication systems, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also discusses spectrum sensing and handoff strategies, which are topics related to cognitive radio networks, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a likely category. The paper also discusses the design parameters of cognitive radio networks, which is a topic related to system design and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of energy efficiency in multimedia communication, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category.
